LatexCommand ref
reference "A.5 Treatment effects on agro-dealer operations"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

).
 Sales volume is measured as the self-reported total quantity sold of the four most popular high-yielding maize varieties in the previous season (Longe 7H,
 Longe 10H,
 Longe 4,
 and Longe 5).
 Agro-dealers also reported the start-of-season sales price for each variety;
 we use the average of these prices.
 Revenue is calculated by multiplying quantities sold by prices and summing across varieties.
 Additional outcomes include the number of customers purchasing maize seed per day at the start of the season and the number of maize varieties stocked.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The intervention increases business activity.
 At midline,
 treated agro-dealers score significantly higher on the 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "anderson2008multiple"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 index,
 and revenue increases by nearly 20%,
 significant at the 10% level.
 The revenue increase coincides with a larger rise in sales volumes (28.4% relative to baseline) than in prices (2.3% relative to baseline),
 although neither component is individually statistically significant,
 suggesting that higher revenue primarily reflects increased demand rather than price adjustments.
 At endline,
 the overall index is significantly higher at the 1% level,
 driven primarily by a 31% increase in the number of customers served – approximately six additional customers per day.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results show that increased farmer engagement translates into higher business activity among agro-dealers.
 Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "A.5 Treatment effects on agro-dealer operations"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 reports business outcomes for two recently released maize varieties (Longe 10H and Longe 5),
 further supporting the positive impact on agro-dealer business activity.
\end_layout

